{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1800,"text":"When I was a kid,\nmy parents would tell me,"},{"time":4640,"text":"\"You can make a mess,\nbut you have to clean up after yourself.\""},{"time":8440,"text":"So freedom came with responsibility."},{"time":11800,"text":"But my imagination would take me\nto all these wonderful places,"},{"time":15400,"text":"where everything was possible."},{"time":17520,"text":"So I grew up in a bubble of innocence --"},{"time":20440,"text":"or a bubble of ignorance, I should say,"},{"time":22800,"text":"because adults would lie to us\nto protect us from the ugly truth."},{"time":27920,"text":"And growing up, I found out\nthat adults make a mess,"},{"time":31520,"text":"and they're not very good\nat cleaning up after themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35360,"text":"Fast forward, I am an adult now,"},{"time":37520,"text":"and I teach citizen science and invention\nat the Hong Kong Harbour School."},{"time":42520,"text":"And it doesn't take too long"},{"time":43880,"text":"before my students walk on a beach\nand stumble upon piles of trash."},{"time":48120,"text":"So as good citizens,\nwe clean up the beaches --"},{"time":50800,"text":"and no, he is not drinking alcohol,\nand if he is, I did not give it to him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":57960,"text":"And so it's sad to say,"},{"time":59200,"text":"but today more than 80 percent \nof the oceans have plastic in them."},{"time":63000,"text":"It's a horrifying fact."},{"time":64800,"text":"And in past decades,"},{"time":66200,"text":"we've been taking those big ships out\nand those big nets,"},{"time":69680,"text":"and we collect those plastic bits\nthat we look at under a microscope,"},{"time":73040,"text":"and we sort them,"},{"time":74280,"text":"and then we put this data onto a map."},{"time":76440,"text":"But that takes forever,\nit's very expensive,"},{"time":78800,"text":"and so it's quite risky\nto take those big boats out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81960,"text":"So with my students, ages six to 15,"},{"time":84920,"text":"we've been dreaming\nof inventing a better way."},{"time":87160,"text":"So we've transformed our tiny\nHong Kong classroom into a workshop."},{"time":91600,"text":"And so we started building\nthis small workbench,"},{"time":94280,"text":"with different heights,\nso even really short kids can participate."},{"time":97480,"text":"And let me tell you, kids with power tools\nare awesome and safe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":103040,"text":"Not really."},{"time":104960,"text":"And so, back to plastic."},{"time":106200,"text":"We collect this plastic and we grind it\nto the size we find it in the ocean,"},{"time":109840,"text":"which is very small\nbecause it breaks down."},{"time":112040,"text":"And so this is how we work."},{"time":113440,"text":"I let the imaginations\nof my students run wild."},{"time":116600,"text":"And my job is to try to collect\nthe best of each kid's idea"},{"time":120880,"text":"and try to combine it into something\nthat hopefully would work."},{"time":125920,"text":"And so we have agreed\nthat instead of collecting plastic bits,"},{"time":129080,"text":"we are going to collect only the data."},{"time":131080,"text":"So we're going to get an image\nof the plastic with a robot --"},{"time":134080,"text":"so robots, kids get very excited."},{"time":136480,"text":"And the next thing we do --\nwe do what we call \"rapid prototyping.\""},{"time":139647,"text":"We are so rapid at prototyping"},{"time":141360,"text":"that the lunch is still in the lunchbox\nwhen we're hacking it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":145880,"text":"And we hack table lamps and webcams,\ninto plumbing fixtures"},{"time":150160,"text":"and we assemble that into a floating robot\nthat will be slowly moving through water"},{"time":155320,"text":"and through the plastic\nthat we have there --"},{"time":157440,"text":"and this is the image\nthat we get in the robot."},{"time":159655,"text":"So we see the plastic pieces\nfloating slowly through the sensor,"},{"time":163400,"text":"and the computer on board\nwill process this image,"},{"time":166720,"text":"and measure the size of each particle,"},{"time":168840,"text":"so we have a rough estimate\nof how much plastic there is in the water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173520,"text":"So we documented\nthis invention step by step"},{"time":176560,"text":"on a website for inventors\ncalled Instructables,"},{"time":179960,"text":"in the hope that somebody\nwould make it even better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183838,"text":"What was really cool about this project\nwas that the students saw a local problem,"},{"time":187720,"text":"and boom -- they are trying\nto immediately address it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190411,"text":"[I can investigate my local problem]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":192760,"text":"But my students in Hong Kong\nare hyperconnected kids."},{"time":196000,"text":"And they watch the news,\nthey watch the Internet,"},{"time":198320,"text":"and they came across this image."},{"time":201840,"text":"This was a child, probably under 10,\ncleaning up an oil spill bare-handed,"},{"time":206600,"text":"in the Sundarbans, which is the world's\nlargest mangrove forest in Bangladesh."},{"time":211120,"text":"So they were very shocked,"},{"time":213600,"text":"because this is the water they drink,\nthis is the water they bathe in,"},{"time":216920,"text":"this is the water they fish in --\nthis is the place where they live."},{"time":220320,"text":"And also you can see the water is brown,\nthe mud is brown and oil is brown,"},{"time":224240,"text":"so when everything is mixed up,"},{"time":225741,"text":"it's really hard to see\nwhat's in the water."},{"time":228240,"text":"But, there's a technology\nthat's rather simple,"},{"time":230520,"text":"that's called spectrometry,"},{"time":232080,"text":"that allows you see what's in the water."},{"time":234009,"text":"So we built a rough prototype\nof a spectrometer,"},{"time":237080,"text":"and you can shine light\nthrough different substances"},{"time":240040,"text":"that produce different spectrums,"},{"time":242480,"text":"so that can help you\nidentify what's in the water."},{"time":246360,"text":"So we packed this prototype of a sensor,"},{"time":249280,"text":"and we shipped it to Bangladesh."},{"time":251989,"text":"So what was cool about this project"},{"time":253680,"text":"was that beyond addressing\na local problem,"},{"time":256839,"text":"or looking at a local problem,"},{"time":258293,"text":"my students used their empathy\nand their sense of being creative"},{"time":262240,"text":"to help, remotely, other kids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264520,"text":"[I can investigate a remote problem]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":266259,"text":"So I was very compelled\nby doing the second experiments,"},{"time":268903,"text":"and I wanted to take it even further --"},{"time":271440,"text":"maybe addressing an even harder problem,\nand it's also closer to my heart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276560,"text":"So I'm half Japanese and half French,"},{"time":279200,"text":"and maybe you remember in 2011\nthere was a massive earthquake in Japan."},{"time":285120,"text":"It was so violent that it triggered\nseveral giant waves --"},{"time":288960,"text":"they are called tsunami --"},{"time":290400,"text":"and those tsunami destroyed many cities\non the eastern coast of Japan."},{"time":298680,"text":"More than 14,000 people\ndied in an instant."},{"time":303600,"text":"Also, it damaged the nuclear\npower plant of Fukushima,"},{"time":307360,"text":"the nuclear power plant just by the water."},{"time":310480,"text":"And today, I read the reports"},{"time":312920,"text":"and an average of 300 tons"},{"time":316000,"text":"are leaking from the nuclear power plant\ninto the Pacific Ocean."},{"time":319600,"text":"And today the whole Pacific Ocean\nhas traces of contamination of cesium-137."},{"time":326000,"text":"If you go outside on the West Coast,\nyou can measure Fukushima everywhere."},{"time":330440,"text":"But if you look at the map,\nit can look like most of the radioactivity"},{"time":333760,"text":"has been washed away\nfrom the Japanese coast,"},{"time":335880,"text":"and most of it is now --\nit looks like it's safe, it's blue."},{"time":338720,"text":"Well, reality is a bit\nmore complicated than this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342160,"text":"So I've been going to Fukushima\nevery year since the accident,"},{"time":345840,"text":"and I measure independently\nand with other scientists,"},{"time":348400,"text":"on land, in the river --"},{"time":350280,"text":"and this time we wanted to take the kids."},{"time":353040,"text":"So of course we didn't take the kids,\nthe parents wouldn't allow that to happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":358200,"text":"But every night we would report\nto \"Mission Control\" --"},{"time":362160,"text":"different masks they're wearing."},{"time":364360,"text":"It could look like they didn't take\nthe work seriously, but they really did"},{"time":368760,"text":"because they're going to have to live\nwith radioactivity their whole life."},{"time":373640,"text":"And so what we did with them"},{"time":375720,"text":"is that we'd discuss the data\nwe collected that day,"},{"time":378360,"text":"and talk about where\nwe should be going next --"},{"time":380575,"text":"strategy, itinerary, etc..."},{"time":382720,"text":"And to do this, we built\na very rough topographical map"},{"time":386360,"text":"of the region around\nthe nuclear power plant."},{"time":389240,"text":"And so we built the elevation map,"},{"time":391280,"text":"we sprinkled pigments to represent\nreal-time data for radioactivity,"},{"time":395920,"text":"and we sprayed water\nto simulate the rainfall."},{"time":400280,"text":"And with this we could see\nthat the radioactive dust"},{"time":403280,"text":"was washing from the top of the mountain\ninto the river system,"},{"time":406360,"text":"and leaking into the ocean."},{"time":407920,"text":"So it was a rough estimate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410680,"text":"But with this in mind,\nwe organized this expedition,"},{"time":413640,"text":"which was the closest civilians have been\nto the nuclear power plant."},{"time":417280,"text":"We are sailing 1.5 kilometers away\nfrom the nuclear power plant,"},{"time":421640,"text":"and with the help of the local fisherman,"},{"time":423617,"text":"we are collecting sediment from the seabed"},{"time":425880,"text":"with a custom sediment sampler\nwe've invented and built."},{"time":429360,"text":"We pack the sediment into small bags,"},{"time":432640,"text":"we then dispatch them\nto hundreds of small bags"},{"time":434920,"text":"that we send to different universities,"},{"time":436880,"text":"and we produce the map\nof the seabed radioactivity,"},{"time":439880,"text":"especially in estuaries\nwhere the fish will reproduce,"},{"time":442440,"text":"and I will hope that we will have improved"},{"time":444520,"text":"the safety of the local fishermen\nand of your favorite sushi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":448960,"text":"You can see a progression here --"},{"time":450560,"text":"we've gone from a local problem\nto a remote problem to a global problem."},{"time":455120,"text":"And it's been super exciting\nto work at these different scales,"},{"time":458097,"text":"with also very simple,\nopen-source technologies."},{"time":461680,"text":"But at the same time,\nit's been increasingly frustrating"},{"time":465040,"text":"because we have only started to measure\nthe damage that we have done."},{"time":468760,"text":"We haven't even started\nto try to solve the problems."},{"time":473640,"text":"And so I wonder\nif we should just take a leap"},{"time":476440,"text":"and try to invent better ways\nto do all these things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481520,"text":"And so the classroom\nstarted to feel a little bit small,"},{"time":485120,"text":"so we found an industrial\nsite in Hong Kong,"},{"time":487840,"text":"and we turned it into\nthe largest mega-space"},{"time":491120,"text":"focused on social\nand environmental impact."},{"time":494320,"text":"It's in central Hong Kong,"},{"time":495640,"text":"and it's a place we can work\nwith wood, metal, chemistry,"},{"time":498880,"text":"a bit of biology, a bit of optics,"},{"time":500530,"text":"basically you can build\npretty much everything there."},{"time":503047,"text":"And its a place where\nadults and kids can play together."},{"time":506040,"text":"It's a place where\nkids' dreams can come true,"},{"time":509640,"text":"with the help of adults,"},{"time":511000,"text":"and where adults can be kids again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512840,"text":"Student: Acceleration! Acceleration!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":516000,"text":"Cesar Harada: We're asking\nquestions such as,"},{"time":518159,"text":"can we invent the future of mobility\nwith renewable energy?"},{"time":521000,"text":"For example."},{"time":523320,"text":"Or, can we help the mobility\nof the aging population"},{"time":527640,"text":"by transforming very standard wheelchairs\ninto cool, electric vehicles?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":533240,"text":"So plastic, oil and radioactivity\nare horrible, horrible legacies,"},{"time":539800,"text":"but the very worst legacy\nthat we can leave our children is lies."},{"time":544760,"text":"We can no longer afford\nto shield the kids from the ugly truth"},{"time":550000,"text":"because we need their imagination\nto invent the solutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554720,"text":"So citizen scientists, makers, dreamers --"},{"time":559720,"text":"we must prepare the next generation"},{"time":562440,"text":"that cares about\nthe environment and people,"},{"time":565520,"text":"and that can actually\ndo something about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568200,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569440,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}